Installing IntelliJ IDEA on OS X:
- Download the IntelliJ IDEA community edition
- Install it
- After installation select the default option
- Then need to tell the IDE where is the JDK is
-------------------
- In the "Welcome to IntelliJ IDEA" screen
- Click on "Configure" -> "Project Defaults" -> "Project Structure
- Go to "Platforms Settings" -> Select "SDKs"
- Click '+' -> click JDK
- Browse to JDK folder (not the JRE folder)
- Now select the left side "Project" option
- Select the "Project SDK" to 1.8
- And "Project Language" level to "8 - Lambdas, type annotations etc."
- Click OK
- Now check the "Name" field to be set to the version of java number
